description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking to expand your skills and enhance your career to include providing Complex Clinical Care or do you already have Complex Care experience?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare are seeking experienced Health Care Assistants to support a young woman with complex care needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dedicated and compassionate Healthcare Assistants who are passionate about their job, enjoy delivering one to one support and who can build positive relationships with our service users and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Our service user requires a Health Care Assistant to support her with clinical interventions and social support whilst maintaining her safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;She has severe learning disabilities and is unable to communicate verbally, body language and gestures are how she makes her needs known.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;She enjoys social outings, participating in arts and crafts and sensory play.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It would be ideal if you had experience with challenging behaviors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 6 months previous care experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Medication Administration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Personal Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Moving and Handling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• PEG Feeding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Learning Disability Awareness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Managing Challenging Behaviours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Part Time Days (10am - 4pm)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Waking Nights (10pm – 7:45am)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on her day to day life.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
